9:
Judah is like a young lion that has returned to its den satisfiedafter eating the animals that it has killed.
He is like a lion that lies down and stretches out after eating;
no one would dare to disturb it.

11:
The grapevines of his descendants will produce grapes very abundantly.As a result, they will not object to tying their young donkeys to the grapevines in order that they can eat the leaves of the grapevines.
Wine will be very plentiful, with the result that they will wash their clothes in wine;
they will wash their cloaks in wine that is as red as blood.
